I notice the Savage has several abilities which increase their defensive attributes like parry and evade. What i want to know is when it says 25% bonus to parry or evade does that equate to a 25% bonus overall or a bonus of 25% of what you already have<br>
IE with Swiftness of Kelegor 6 would a 50 savage have a combined 25% chance to evade (20% + 1/4th of 20%) or 45% chance to evade (20% + 25%)?<br>
<br>
Also why is it that Midgard, the supposed melee realm, gets penalised for having weapon duality (IE 2 damage types under same spec, or One and Two handed weapons under same spec) when Hibernia, the suposed magic realm, isnt?<br>
<br>
Also is it confirmed Savages are Dex Quick Str? They sound more like a rogue class to me with them stat increases. Theres an idea, put them in Rogues give them minstrel like stealth and 2points per spec hehe<br>
Not getting any Con is gonna hurt the savage. Low str will also hurt if the weapons are infact STR DEX based. I had intended to make a Kobold savage 'cos the thought of the little blue guy being primative and 'savage' to me was funny, but i think i will go with the Norse now for the higher starting str and con to help with damage and hps  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#000000>(11/21/02 7:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> They tell me the Evade/Parry buffs are additional, not multipliers.   They effectively add +% to the chance to parry, not multiply the percentages.<br>
<br>
In your example, the Savage would have 45% chance to Evade.<br>
<br>
I don't know what you mean by HTH being penalized.  Speccing in this one line means we reduce damage variance on both slash and thrust, we increase chance to dual/triple/quad hit, and we get our styles... this is akin to speccing in Thrust, Slash, AND Celtic Dual in Hibernia.<br>
<br>
And finally - yes.  Our stats are currently QUI / DEX / STR.  I've asked that they be changed to DEX / QUI / STR and that we be given an innate, passive CON buff that caps at +32 at level 40.  This would help us with our HP concerns while leaving all the versatility for our spec choices. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jonthan>Jonthan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(11/22/02 9:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> <br>
So if someone pretty much neglects parry and doesnt spec in it, via the savagery buff they can still have 30% parry for 30 seconds?<br>
I can understand 1.5spec points if thats the case. Letting a class spec to 40odd parry along with a buff that gives a 25% bonus would seem a bit much<br>
Was there any recast time on the savages buffs?<br>
<br>
This inherant passive +32con buff at 40 you talk about, is it like say the equivilent of a baseline buff that has to be cast or is it with you all the time? What about rather than a con buff they give savages something akin to a Hero's stagform? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#000000>(11/22/02 9:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> The CON suggestion I have would just be a constant thing...<br>
<br>
There's no recast timer on your buffs.  The only caveat is that when you recast them before they drop, they incur the health charge of the previous activation immediately.<br>
<br>
And yeah.. if a level 50 with 1 in parry has a 5% chance to parry, then with the 25% buff they'll have a 30% chance... along with their 45% chance to Evade (Evade IV + 25%). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jonthan>Jonthan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(11/24/02 8:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> Might have some problems getting them to agree to what would essentially be seen by others as a forth stat that increases as you level. Champions would probably complain that they had to spec in a line to get their constitution buffed up. But then giving Savages a str con buff like the champion wouldnt be so bad, tho it doesnt seem to be inline with what savagery does<br>
<br>
Still Savages sound like they're gonna be a nice little package, low on hps but defensively on par, if not better, than the main tanks of the realm (Esp with the way evade is at the moment)<br>
It'll be hard to decide what type to play, a mean little whirling dervish of a kobold or a Troll/Norse with a big Axe that parrys and evades like a &lt;bleep&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#000000>(11/25/02 4:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> Right now I'm actually suggesting they leave the setup as it currently stands.  The only change I'm asking for is that they make sure the Savage is on the heavy tank HP table.  That should be enough to get us going, at least, for testing purposes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jonthan>Jonthan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(11/28/02 7:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savagery and other stuff</span><hr size=1> I was thinking that another option to address a savages low hp total, and keeping in line with the idea of a savage and the savagery spell line, would be a temporary hp buff that would give you a certain amount of hps for 30 seconds before taking them away again. Probably on a 10-15minute timer. This would be akin to the Savage faced with death and getting a sudden surge of energy to fight on, but when the energy surge fades away the Savage is left drained and depleted...  Maybe the penalty for using this 'get out of jail free card' would be that after it wears off the savage is reduced to 1hp (No matter what they were before or towards the end of the buff) and maybe suffer under effects similar to rez sickness for a minute<br>
The amount of hps returned by the buff would be your savagery total as a percentage of your total hps. Say you had 1200 hps and 50 in savagery, you would get 50% or 600hps back for 30 seconds<br>
<br>
<br>
Just an idea and probably overpowering but hey, i got nothing better to do while i wait for SI to be released <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=10.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=10.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.threadControl?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub79.ezb